    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                
             <pb facs="liv_001729_0001" n="0001"/>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><space extent="3" unit="words"/>Pioneer <placeName><settlement type="village">Maruru</settlement></placeName>
    <lb/><space extent="3" unit="words"/><space extent="1" unit="chars"/><measure>about 1Â° above 
<lb/><space extent="4" unit="words"/><space extent="2" unit="chars"/><placeName><settlement type="village"><persName>Paulo</persName>'s</settlement></placeName></measure> <date when="1862-02-17">17<hi rend="sup underline">th</hi> <choice><abbr>Feby</abbr><expan>February</expan></choice>
<lb/><space extent="6" unit="words"/><space extent="1" unit="chars"/>1862 -</date></p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">My Dear <persName>D<hi rend="sup">r</hi> Kirk</persName></p>
                <lb/><p><space extent="1" unit="words"/><space extent="3" unit="chars"/>Our progress is
<lb/>frightfully slow - creeping &amp; scarcely
<lb/>that - if Vienna would cut wood
<lb/>at <placeName><settlement type="village">Shamo</settlement></placeName> or <placeName><settlement type="village">Bandeira</settlement></placeName> <choice><abbr>D<hi rend="sup underline">o</hi></abbr><expan>Ditto</expan></choice>
<lb/>please make an agreement
<lb/>with them - I fear we shall not
<lb/>get up to <placeName><settlement type="village">Ruo</settlement></placeName> before the <term type="occupation">officers</term>
<lb/>must leave - <persName><term type="occupation">Captain</term> Wilson</persName>
<lb/>wishes your company - &amp;
<lb/>should the <term type="occupation">bishop</term> meet you
<lb/>at <placeName><settlement type="village">Ruo</settlement></placeName> - you will not be so
<lb/>much needed as a <term type="occupation">guide</term> - Wood
<lb/>burned off at frightful rate
<lb/>makes me fear that we must
<lb/>unload part at <placeName><settlement type="village">Shamo</settlement></placeName> or sooner

                <pb facs="liv_001729_0002" n="0002"/>
<!-- No image of this page currently available as it is obscured by frame - it is therefore transcribed by copying an existing transcript (in same frame as page 1 of the letter). This is not ideal as line breaks and other textual formatting features cannot be determined. I have used <supplied> to mark the section thus added - AM-->
<lb/><supplied>We can only go at night <seg type="weather">after the breeze springs up</seg>. I feel very sorry at our slow progress chiefly on account of the friends with us. If <persName><term type="occupation">Captain</term> Wilson</persName> wishes you to go on, and I believe he does at present you may go up to the <term type="occupation">Bishops</term>. We are all well <persName>Meller</persName> a little better</supplied></p>
<lb/><closer rend="center"><salute><supplied>I am etc</supplied></salute> <!-- Adrian, I'm pretty sure this etc would be the &amp;c, but cannot be sure...should we code even the postscript as supplied as well? HB --><!-- If we're adhering to the transcript, we'd better just do so and can always correct if we get to see the letter. AW -->
<lb/><signed rend="center"><hi><supplied>David Livingstone</supplied></hi></signed></closer>
<lb/><postscript><p><supplied>We cannot do without <persName>Rae</persName> if we unload he must help us <persName><term type="occupation">Captain</term> Wilson</persName> will give him a few provisions to last till we come. We hope to near <placeName><settlement type="village">Mazaro</settlement></placeName> tonight</supplied></p></postscript>
               
